./sdp/logs/Verify_T-010_20260416T181925Z_1776384834.log:8574:+{"type":"message","timestamp":"2026-04-16T21:35:48.623Z","role":"user","content":"# Verification: Task T-023@20260416T054258Z\n\n**Task:** Add course-driven self-critique and revision targets.\n**Tier:** T2\n\nYou are the VERIFY agent for this task. The LEAD agent has completed their work.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- critique output names concrete course concepts behind failures, such as masking, no recurrence, no cadence, weak transition, over-compression, or unsupported density<br/>- bounded revision can adjust form, harmony, rhythm, register, mix, or strategy without changing piece identity<br/>- tests verify at least one metric improves after revision\n\n## Review Checklist\n\n1. **Review recent commits:**\n   ```bash\n   git log --oneline -5\n   git diff HEAD~3 --stat\n   ```\n\n2. **Review code changes:**\n   ```bash\n   git diff HEAD~3\n   ```\n\n3. **Review specification** (if T2/T3):\n   Read `specs/t-023@20260416t054258z-spec.md`\n\n4. **Check ESCALATIONS.md** for any flagged issues.\n\n5. **Run the test suite:**\n   ```bash\n   pip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x\n   ```\n\n## Evaluation Criteria\n\nEvaluate the work against these five dimensions:\n\n1. **Correctness**: Does the output match the requirements/spec?\n2. **Completeness**: Are there gaps, missing edge cases, or unhandled scenarios?\n3. **Consistency**: Does the output follow established patterns and conventions?\n4. **Security**: Are there vulnerabilities, leaked secrets, or unsafe practices?\n5. **Quality**: Does the output meet the quality gates for this phase?\n\n## Output\n\nWrite your verification report and all findings to this exact path:\n`sdp/verification/t-023@20260416t054258z-verify.md`\nDo not use a different filename or directory.\n\nUse this format:\n\n```markdown\n# Verification Report — T-023@20260416T054258Z\n\n**Verify Agent:** [your agent name]\n**Date:** [today]\n**Artifacts Reviewed:** [list files re