+## frac-0029 (2026-05-02)
+
+- **Reason:** Accompaniment depth and startup-hardening scope assumptions
+- **Details:** Exploration found the affected runtime surface is `my-claw/tools/senseweave/synthesis/accompaniment.py`, with existing coverage in `tests/test_accompaniment.py` and live pattern helpers for density tracking, accompaniment type selection, six accompaniment figures, pedal points, breathing swells, and transition decisions. The module already produces meaningful note tuples end-to-end but classifies at fractal depth 1 (`13/18 trivial, 5 real`) because the one-return pattern helpers outnumber real logic. This task preserves every existing helper and tuple contract while adding a stdlib-only typed accompaniment snapshot/report/summary surface that delegates to the existing selection, breathing, pedal, and `get_pattern(...)` paths. The generated startup hardening bullets for `bootstrap_identity()` ordering and standalone/federated persistence target the daemon identity subsystem; the current tree already calls `bootstrap_identity()` before `FirstBootAnnouncer` in both daemon startup paths and has `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` plus `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` as regression anchors. No new dependencies, migrations, provider secrets, database columns, or agent commands are required.
