 ## Unreleased
 
+- Added depth-2 accompaniment decision report helpers (frac-0029): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/synthesis/accompaniment.py` now exposes frozen `AccompanimentPatternSnapshot` and `AccompanimentPlanReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `accompaniment_density_band`, `accompaniment_pattern_name`, `accompaniment_energy_band`, `frequency_register_band`, `accompaniment_transition_mode`, `summarize_pattern_events`, `build_pattern_snapshot`, `build_accompaniment_plan_report`, and `summarize_accompaniment_plan_report` so composer/operator diagnostics can resolve the existing inverse-density accompaniment path into a JSON-safe decision summary. Existing `DensityTracker`, selection, six pattern helpers, pedal, breathing, transition, and tuple contracts are preserved; `tests/test_accompaniment_depth.py` pins band cutpoints, pattern snapshot aggregation, end-to-end density/breathing/pedal report output, JSON-safe summaries, agreement with the existing helpers, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_accompaniment.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
